HEADWORD: Spearfish
<hw>Spear"fish`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<sd>(a)</sd> <def>A large and powerful fish (<spn>Tetrapturus
albidus</spn>) related to the swordfish, but having scales and ventral
fins. It is found on the American coast and the Mediterranean.</def>
<sd>(b)</sd> <def>The carp sucker.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

